entry.title: Enable cardboard runtime to build by default
entry.content:
When this initially landed building was disabled by default as the

implementation wasn't even far enough along for a reasonable runtime

flag to guard the feature. While still missing some parity with the

existing GVR runtime, the implementation is at least at a reasonable

point to include it in the build to ease testing and development.



The cardboard runtime increases the size of the binary by 76kb; but

this is actually smaller than the ARCore runtime and long term will

enable us to remove the VR DFM, and will improve the reach and

performance of WebXR/VR overall.



Given that the default conditions for enabling all of the WebXR Android

supported runtimes are the same, this change also abstracts that to

a separate, more easily modifiable arg that the other parameters all

reference. The intention here is to provide some re-use, while also

allowing other embedders the ability to toggle specific runtimes on or

off via overrides.



Bug: 989117

entry.title: Support automatic beacons on Android context menu navigations.
entry.content:
A prior CL allowed automatic beacons to be sent from a fenced frame if a

top-level navigation happened from a contextual menu (i.e. right

clicking on a link and selecting 'Open Link in New Tab')[1]. While that

allows `reserved.top_navigation` automatic beacons to work properly with

contextual menus on desktop platforms, it does not allow the same on

Android.



This is because Android has a separate path for building contextual

menus, and does not pass in the initiator frame token or process ID,

both of which are needed for automatic beacons to work properly[2].



Luckily, this information is already being plumbed through the Android

contextual menu code[3]. However, it only is sent in the context of

Attribution Reporting impressions[4], and will not be in place outside

of that use case.



This CL allows the initiator frame token and the initiator process ID to

be sent even if an impression is not present, and has it always send

those values as long as they exist. This also converts the Java

Impression class into a new a new helper class called

AdditionalNavigationParams. The impression-specific parameters will only

be populated if an impression exists in the navigation. This is done to

organize the needed parameters into one place, to allow for easier

expansion, and to avoid cluttering the ContextMenuParams class.



After this change, by the time

RenderFrameHostImpl::MaybeSendFencedFrameReportingBeacon is called, the

initiator frame token and initiator process ID will be in the navigation

request object the same way it currently is on desktop versions.



The important test changes for this CL are in

ContextMenuLoadUrlParamsTest.java.

[2]https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:content/browser/renderer_host/render_frame_host_impl.cc;l=8406-8416;drc=bcd0b9f6b615432f56ce33805286f44da24efc6f

[3]https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/4538633

[4]https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:content/public/android/java/src/org/chromium/content_public/browser/Impression.java

entry.title: Explicitly pass the reference box to SVG transform calculation
entry.content:
Since computing the stroke bounding box - as used for

'transform-box: stroke-box' - requires the children of a container (or

with the existing UpdateTransformAfterLayout()) and use that in the two

subclasses. In other cases just rely on the shared implementation in

TransformHelper, and explicitly compute and pass in the reference box.

entry.content:

missing await was meaning that certain tests were ending prematurely, so

we add it. Second, we allow tests to wait until the server has received

multiple reports. Finally, we separate the external tests into a

different virtual test suite without developer mode; this ensures that

those tests' reports will not be immediately sent, preventing them from

interfering with the internal tests.



As a drive-by, we add an api field to verifyReports() to support future

Protected Audience tests.

entry.title: Cookie Policy: Disable 3PC when default content setting is block
entry.content:
When the default cookie setting is set to BLOCK, the Block 3PC

preference is meaningless - it can never impact access decisions.



For enterprise policies, we can easily surface this relationship to

users by following the standard enterprise pattern and disabling

3PC with policy indicators on affected controls.



To avoid requiring each UI surface which represents the 3PC setting

state to check multiple locations for management information, this

CL updates the policy handler to simply set the block 3PC pref

directly, so it naturally appears managed.



This does not change the semantics of any policies, but simply makes

representing the effective state to users easier.

entry.title: Prefetch: Keep prefetch queued when at the limit
entry.content:
Currently, when we've reached the limit of number of completed

prefetches and we can't evict any prefetches to make room, we destroy

the queued prefetch under consideration. This CL updates this

behaviour, and now keeps the prefetch under consideration queued, and

tries to find another prefetch.



This CL also tries to trigger a new prefetch anytime an existing

prefetch is destroyed, to deal with a scenario where a prefetch times

out and we have other prefetches queued up. This could cause a

potential rentrancy into PrefetchService::Prefetch() when we evict

while trying to consider if a prefetch can be started, so we no longer

evict in CanPrefetchNow(), but only when we're about to start the

next prefetch.

entry.title: Simplify IsMinimumAddress().
entry.content:
Currently, IsMinimumAddress() is two unnecessary parameters:

- app_locale: It's only used to construct an AutofillCountry object in

GetAutofillProfileRequirementResult(). However, the optional

app_locale parameter is only needed to translate the country name.

If AutofillCountry::name() is not used, like in the case of checking

requirements, it can be omitted.

- predicted_country_code: All callsites use the profile's country.*

This CL removes them both.



* There's some historical context why it was added in the first place,

and why it is no longer necessary. In the past, complementing the

country happened before the multi-step import logic. So during multi-

step imports (which checks address requirements too), it was necessary

to recompute the complemented country whenever something was merged.

[1] changed this behavior and swapped the order. Since then, by the

any time requirements are checked, the country is already

complemented.



[1] https://docs.google.com/document/d/1bwgKfCeDdXVMghgDdnJ0Mla-GW8DP2IbMz3mwO_ifk0/edit?resourcekey=0-jr163i3QOo9yrKW3j9yWDA#heading=h.v2wyouz52iot

entry.title: [DBSC] Check if the /RotateBoundCookies sets the required cookies
entry.content:
The cookie header is not present in the response of the cookie rotation

request that is propagated from the network to the browser process.



Unexpected server response i.e. not setting the required cookies is

considered a persistent error.



This CL adds a cookie observer to the rotation request. The observer is

called with `network::mojom::CookieAccessDetails::Type::kChange` with

cookies set in the response of the request if there are any. The cookies

are verified to contain the required cookie.



Normally, a cookie update notification should be sent before the request

is complete. We add some leeway using a timer in the case mojo messages

are delivered out of order.
